# CSS Conventions

## Logical properties only

Always use CSS logical properties instead of physical ones:

| Physical (do not use) | Logical (use this) |
|-----------------------|-------------------|
| `margin-left` | `margin-inline-start` |
| `margin-right` | `margin-inline-end` |
| `margin-top` | `margin-block-start` |
| `padding: 12px 16px` | `padding-block: 12px; padding-inline: 16px;` |
| `width` | `inline-size` |
| `height` | `block-size` |
| `min-height` | `min-block-size` |
| `max-width` | `max-inline-size` |
| `top` | `inset-block-start` |
| `border-left` | `border-inline-start` |

Exceptions: `border-radius`, `box-shadow`, `line-height`, `@media (min-width:)` — these have no logical equivalents.

## Design tokens

- All colors via MUI theme or `var(--color-*)` custom properties — never hardcode colors
- Light/dark theme tokens defined via MUI `createTheme()` with palette overrides
- Semantic token naming: `--color-passed`, `--color-failed`, `--color-warning`, `--color-critical`
- Component-specific tokens: `--color-badge-*`, `--color-status-*`, `--color-priority-*`

## Inline styles in JSX

When using inline styles in React components (or MUI `sx` prop), also use logical properties (e.g. `marginInlineStart` not `marginLeft`).
